  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. The model is intended to predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification is performed; all 13 credibility factors have been assessed and the overall determination is Accepted at Low assurance. The intended use scope — steady-state operating envelope 2000–3500 RPM, 2–6 L/min flow, 37 °C blood analog — is described in the bound requirement and claim documents. Note: structured hasContextOfUse linkage is not provided under the Minimal profile; use-scope information must be retrieved from the referenced requirement and claim resources.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/vad-hemolysis-mrl5-cou2",
